title: Make or update a rural payments claim

heading_context: Make or update a rural payments claim
chunks.html_content:
Sign in to make a rural payments claim or update your details. If you do not already have an account, you can register for one.

You can use the service to:

  • apply for Countryside Stewardship grants
  • apply for the Sustainable Farming Incentive (SFI)
  • view your Basic Payment Scheme (BPS) entitlements and previous claims
  • update your personal and business details
  • check and update digital maps of your registered land
  • give someone permission to act on your behalf

Register for an account by calling the Rural Payments helpline.

You’ll be sent a Customer Reference Number (CRN) which you can use to sign in.

chunks.html_content:
There’s a different way to apply for rural payments and grants if:

  • your farm is in Scotland
  • your farm is in Wales
  • your farm is in Northern Ireland
